			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Btw i believe hes talking about Instant Gate potions (pot=potion). They are quite usefull, Anyways, hats off to Iuar since he knows what its like on probobly the toughest pvp server out there, SUllon Zek. Now yes i know u cant have items looted from you or anything but notice how on Rallos you see things like Organized attempts to kill the sleeper, multiple Time enabled guilds, etc. On all PvP servers if you want to raid a mob and another team knows about it? guess what, your screwed. Ive had massive raids of 80 people turn into massive pvp events of 80vs80 making one hell of a warzone.
<br />

<br />
Mages dont suck PvP, if they know what they are doing. First of all, pet burn is quite a large part of it at high level pvp. We have a hard time and people get frustrated because for one, our nukes are easy to resist, our mala is a small debuffer(unless player relying on sometihng like protection of seasons...mala overwrites if ya dindt kno), and pets get rooted as if nothing. The whole  earth pet root with -30mr check is really quite useless, its still resisted by any even unless massively debuffed by you and an enchanter for exmaple.
<br />

<br />
Of course every class is handled differently, wizards are a big no no for nuke fights. Play the oor game, the LoS game anything, to stop them from nuking you. They will cut through your resists unless your sporting some EP and time gear(if you are u should know what ur doing by now). Id recomend the Air Pet, as the stun still has a considerable chance to land. Our 65 Nuke Sun Vortex, seems to me , to have some sort of random resist counter.... basically what i mean is it can be resisted or not.. regardless of what the resists are. Ive had it resisted by a character 20 levels lower than me, and then had it do 75% of their life in one shot. But Sun Vortex probobly still your best bet. And one of the biggest things... Get yourself a rune if at all possible. Either borrow a buff, or do some old time SSRA raids. Shield of Auras or The helm off High Priest arent too bad. Only other thing i can think of is, if u have a chance to take root off ur pet, do it, its definitly worth it. Brining Your pet back is at least, another spell or two that your opponent has to worry about.<br />_________________<br />~Ladine~
<br />
65 Mage of Sullon Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
